17:37.540 --> 17:47.540
may precede the Harper edition with a 500-copy edition of our own, and we may
precede the Harper edition by three or four months, and our edition would then

17:47.540 --> 18:03.820
be signed and numbered and of a very high quality binding and like that. But by
and large, our whole business is to publish hardcovers and be the first

18:03.820 --> 18:12.420
hardcover edition publisher. That's essentially because we're publishing for
collectors and they want hardcovers and they want first editions. And that's why

18:12.420 --> 18:23.460
a number of our books are signed and numbered for the same reason. Right. Okay.
