22:04.960 --> 22:18.740
published Philip K. Dick and that bibliography which is annotated and has 200
reproductions of covers is a bibliography like none other. We think it's the

22:18.740 --> 22:29.680
best bibliography of any author that has ever been published. It's actually more
than a bibliography. It deserves a new name and it's primarily due to the work

22:29.680 --> 22:38.400
of Daniel Levack, who's not only a good bibliographer, but he organizes the
projects and he

22:38.400 --> 22:50.200
essentially got in touch with us and he offered his services, which were very
good indeed. And we went along with it simply because he was very eager to do it

22:50.200 --> 23:03.740
and willing to do it. And neither Chuck nor I are bibliographers, but this
fellow was. And he liked what we liked. And, again, the connection was a

23:03.740 --> 23:13.820
personal connection, not a business connection. We're not doing bibliographies
because there's a lot of money in it. There isn't. But we're doing it simply

23:13.820 --> 23:24.700
because we enjoy doing it, and we enjoy working with this fellow, Levack, who
deserves an award of some kind for this Philip K. Dick, which he just put

23:24.700 --> 23:35.680
together and was published. And we'll be continuing because, essentially, he's
doing more. He's got two or three more that he's completed, and, essentially,

23:35.700 --> 23:44.680
we're publishing them because he's doing them, and that's the main reason. okay
